  "prompt": "Knock knee cause any problem in Delhi police si selection?",
  "response": "Knock knees, or genu valgum, may be a concern during the medical examination process for the selection of candidates in physical jobs, such as in police services. The criteria for physical fitness can include assessments of various physical conditions, and any condition that affects mobility, strength, or physical performance may be scrutinized.\n\nFor the Delhi Police Sub-Inspector (SI) selection, it is essential to meet specific medical standards set by the recruitment authority. If you have knock knees and are concerned about your eligibility, it would be best to consult with a qualified medical professional who can provide guidance based on your specific condition and the standards set by the Delhi Police.\n\nMake sure to refer to the official notification or guidelines issued by the Delhi Police regarding medical standards for the most accurate and relevant information.",
